{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VshmG8ruJpVsB3aNj9nUa5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Taunt Bet - Capability Baseline\n2\t\n3\tNon-custodial P2P gaming platform on Solana. This document captures current implementation state, architectural constraints, and planning direction.\n4\t\n5\tLast updated: 2026-04-09\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## 1) Product Focus\n10\t\n11\t- Real-money P2P gaming with on-chain settlement and verifiable fairness\n12\t- Progression and retention via challenges, points, and loot crates\n13\t- Referral-driven growth with on-chain earnings\n14\t- Operational safety: pause, monitoring, incident response\n15\t\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\t## 2) Shipped Capabilities\n19\t\n20\t### Games (3 live)\n21\t- **FlipYou** (spec 001) — 1v1, commit-reveal + SlotHashes fairness, custom wagers\n22\t- **Pot Shot / Pot Shot** (spec 101) — Multiplayer weighted-entry pot shot, commit-reveal fairness\n23\t- **Close Call** (spec 100) — Pari-mutuel BTC price prediction, Pyth oracle settlement, minute-boundary candle cache\n24\t\n25\t### On-Chain Programs\n26\t- **Per-game programs**: FlipYou, Pot Shot, Close Call — each independently deployable\n27\t- **Platform program**: PlatformConfig (fee BPS, treasury, pause state), admin-updatable via `update_platform_config`\n28\t- **Shared Rust crate** (`solana/shared/`): Escrow helpers, lifecycle state machine, timeout logic, pause controls, commit-reveal verifier, fee calculation, constants\n29\t- **Operational controls**: `set_paused` (per-game pause/unpause), `timeout_refund` (permissionless liveness guarantee), `force_close` (stuck round recovery)\n30\t\n31\t### Settlement & Workers\n32\t- **PDA watcher**: WebSocket `onAccountChange` for instant join/settle detection\n33\t- **Polling fallback**: 1s interval for resilience, ~3-5s total settlement latency\n34\t- **Close Call clock**: Minute-boundary BTC price capture from Pyth Hermes, automatic round creation and settlement\n35\t- **Retry worker**: Exponential backoff for failed settlement transactions\n36\t- **Event worker**: Status transitions (scheduled -> active -> ended) on 10s poll; current implementation uses legacy Dogpile naming\n37\t\n38\t### Auth & Identity\n39\t- **JWT auth** (spec 007) — Challenge-response via wallet signature, HS256 tokens\n40\t- **Player profiles** (spec 008) — Auto-created on first auth, username with 30-day change cooldown\n41\t- **Player stats**: Games played, total wagered, wins, win rate, win streaks (current + all-time), net PnL, per-game breakdown\n42\t- **Public profiles**: Stats visible to other players (no wallet or transaction history exposed)\n43\t- **Weekly leaderboard**: Volume-based ranking per game type with win rate and PnL\n44\t\n45\t### Fairness & Pricing\n46\t- **Commit-reveal fairness** (spec 006): `SHA256(secret || entropy || PDA || algo_ver)`, public verification endpoints\n47\t- **Wager value rate**: cached global conversion rate used for points USD conversion; current implementation reads SOL/USD from Pyth Hermes\n48\t- **Fee structure**: 500 bps flat to single treasury, on-chain PlatformConfig canonical. CI guard: `scripts/check-fees.sh`\n49\t\n50\t### Reward & Retention\n51\t- **Challenge engine** (spec 400) — Daily/weekly/onboarding challenges, template-based, adapter-driven\n52\t- **Reward economy** (spec 401) — Generic points, multiplier, season, and event model; product labels stay display-only\n53\t- **Points** — Season-scoped balance earned per $ wagered using cached global value rates and active multipliers\n54\t- **Loot crates** — Random drops after settled games (points crates + SOL crates from reward pool)\n55\t- **Reward pool** — Accounting-only ledger, configurable share of platform fees (default 20%)\n56\t- **Events** — Scheduled modifier windows with boosted or overridden multipliers, admin-managed\n57\t- **Completion bonus** — Meta-reward for completing all daily challenges (configurable)\n58\t\n59\t### Growth\n60\t- **Referral system** (spec 300) — Unique codes/links, 1000 bps of fee as referral earnings, on-chain SOL claims, KOL rate overrides\n61\t- **Onboarding chain** — 4-step guided first session (set nickname, play, win, try all game types)\n62\t\n63\t### Backend Infrastructure\n64\t- **Async event queue** (spec 301) — Postgres-backed, `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`, handler registry, exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s), dead-letter after 3 attempts\n65\t- **Event-driven pipeline** — `game.settled` → challenge progress + points + crate drops + pool funding; `profile.username_set` → onboarding challenge progress\n66\t- **Admin API** — Campaign/challenge CRUD, reward config tuning, event scheduling, reward pool monitoring (X-Admin-Key auth)\n67\t- **Rate limiting**: Per-wallet and global rate limits on game creation endpoints\n68\t- **Health endpoint**: `GET /health` — DB connectivity, worker status, unsettled queue depth\n69\t- **Transaction history**: Per-player ledger of on-chain deposits, payouts, refunds with game context\n70\t\n71\t### Cross-Repo Tooling\n72\t- `scripts/verify` — Full lint + typecheck + test across all packages\n73\t- `scripts/deploy-devnet.sh` — Build → deploy → IDL sync → config init → ID verification\n74\t- `scripts/check-program-ids.sh` — Anchor.toml / declare_id! / IDL address consistency\n75\t- `scripts/check-fees.sh` — Fee constant parity across Rust and TypeScript\n76\t- `scripts/sync-idl` — Copy built IDLs from solana/target/ to backend anchor-client\n77\t\n78\t---\n79\t\n80\t## 3) Architecture Direction (Locked)\n81\t\n82\tDecisions are recorded in `docs/DECISIONS.md`. Key constraints:\n83\t\n84\t- **Chain**: Solana only. No multichain.\n85\t- **Custody**: Non-custodial. All money movement on-chain.\n86\t- **Programs**: Standard Anchor, per-game + shared crate. No BOLT ECS, no monolith program.\n87\t- **Fairness**: Commit-reveal + SlotHashes (default). VRF optional for future games, not default infrastructure.\n88\t- **Wallets**: Normal wallet-adapter flow. Privy/embedded wallets evaluated later.\n89\t- **Frontend**: Separate project and team. Backend provides API contracts. See `docs/DECISIONS.md` (2026-04-02).\n90\t- **Backend**: Hono API monolith with event-driven side-effects. Challenge engine extraction to separate service deferred (see `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`).\n91\t\n92\t---\n93\t\n94\t## 4) Trust Boundaries\n95\t\n96\t### On-Chain (source of truth)\n97\t- All money movement (escrow, payout, refund, fee collection)\n98\t- Round settlement outcomes\n99\t- Payout eligibility and claim state\n100\t- Platform config (fee rate, pause state)\n101\t\n102\t### Off-Chain (backend)\n103\t- Secret generation and commitment\n104\t- Settlement submission (permissionless on-chain, but backend holds the secret)\n105\t- Player profiles, stats, transaction history\n106\t- Challenge/reward evaluation and grant\n107\t- Points and reward pool accounting\n108\t- Referral tracking and claim processing\n109\t\n110\t### Rule\n111\tIf it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n112\t\n113\t---\n114\t\n115\t## 5) Near-Term Direction\n116\t\n117\t### In progress\n118\t- **Chat service** (spec 009) — Separate repo (`chat/`), global chat + event feed transport\n119\t- **Events** — Scheduled, admin-managed. Infrastructure shipped under legacy Dogpile naming, needs generic reward-economy migration.\n120\t\n121\t### Next priorities\n122\t- SOL crate payout production hardening (tech debt: review transfer handler before enabling)\n123\t- Challenge pool rotation (M2: per-player daily draws from template pool)\n124\t- Additional verification adapters (streak, volume, unique opponents)\n125\t- KOL-triggered challenge campaigns\n126\t- Quest completion leaderboard\n127\t\n128\t### Explicitly deferred\n129\t- **Crash** (spec 002) — Deferred to Phase 2 (decision 2026-03-30). Real-time multiplier game needs different fairness model.\n130\t- **Future game concepts** (specs 102-105) — Not ideated. Placeholders only.\n131\t- **Custodial balance model** — Not planned.\n132\t- **Multichain** — Not planned.\n133\t- **Token utility / TGE mechanics** — Points are the pre-TGE signal. Token integration is post-launch.\n134\t\n135\t---\n136\t\n137\t## 6) Repo Ownership\n138\t\n139\t| Area | Repo | Ownership |\n140\t|------|------|-----------|\n141\t| On-chain programs | `solana/` submodule | This workspace |\n142\t| Backend API + workers | `backend/` submodule | This workspace |\n143\t| Chat service | `chat/` submodule | This workspace |\n144\t| Telegram bot service | `telegram/` submodule | This workspace |\n145\t| Docs, scripts, E2E | Root repo | This workspace |\n146\t| Frontend | Separate repo | Separate team |\n147\t| Waitlist | `waitlist/` | Separate repo (npm, DigitalOcean) |\n148\t\n149\t---\n150\t\n151\t## 7) Success Metrics\n152\t\n153\t- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n154\t- Game round completion rate\n155\t- Challenge completion rate and reward ROI (SOL spent per $ additional wager volume)\n156\t- Referral conversion rate\n157\t- Points/crate engagement (% of active players interacting with challenge UI)\n158\t- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n159\t\n160\t---\n161\t\n162\t## 8) Spec Index\n163\t\n164\t### Shipped (Done)\n165\t| Spec | Name | Notes |\n166\t|------|------|-------|\n167\t| 001 | FlipYou | Shipped, hybrid fairness |\n168\t| 006 | Fairness Backend | Shipped |\n169\t| 007 | JWT Session Auth | Shipped |\n170\t| 008 | User Profile | Shipped (redesigned 2026-03-12) |\n171\t| 100 | Close Call | Shipped, Pyth oracle |\n172\t| 101 | Pot Shot | Shipped |\n173\t| 200 | Visual Regression | Shipped (frontend deferred) |\n174\t| 203 | E2E Integration | Active |\n175\t| 300 | Referral System | Shipped |\n176\t| 301 | Async Event Queue | Shipped |\n177\t| 400 | Challenge Engine | Shipped M1 |\n178\t\n179\t### Active\n180\t| Spec | Name | Notes |\n181\t|------|------|-------|\n182\t| 004 | Shared Infrastructure | Living doc, on-chain lifecycle patterns |\n183\t| 009 | Chat | In progress, separate service |\n184\t| 302 | Telegram Bot | Draft, stateless v1 bot + Telegram share flow |\n185\t| 999 | Enhancements | Rolling backlog |\n186\t\n187\t### Deferred\n188\t| Spec | Name | Notes |\n189\t|------|------|-------|\n190\t| 002 | Crash | Phase 2 (decision 2026-03-30) |\n191\t| 102-105 | Future games | Not ideated, placeholders |\n192\t\n193\t### Out of Scope (frontend)\n194\t| Spec | Name | Notes |\n195\t|------|------|-------|\n196\t| 204 | Multi-Page Flows | Frontend team |\n197\t| 205 | Real Wallet | Frontend team |\n198\t\n199\t### Archived / Superseded\n200\t| Spec | Name | Notes |\n201\t|------|------|-------|\n202\t| 003 | Platform Core | Superseded by DESIGN_REFERENCE.md |\n203\t| 005 | Hybrid Fairness | Superseded by DECISIONS.md (2026-03-11) + spec 006 |\n204\t| 201 | Unit Tests | Covered by FOUNDATIONS.md testing methodology |\n205\t| 202 | Component Tests | Covered by FOUNDATIONS.md testing methodology |\n206\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"14342bb0-1390-4a1f-96f8-b2235d0b347d","uuid":"03151d4f-d27f-47cc-ae40-3e0c4ccc135f","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:43:56.432Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/SCOPE.md","content":"# Taunt Bet - Capability Baseline\n\nNon-custodial P2P gaming platform on Solana. This document captures current implementation state, architectural constraints, and planning direction.\n\nLast updated: 2026-04-09\n\n---\n\n## 1) Product Focus\n\n- Real-money P2P gaming with on-chain settlement and verifiable fairness\n- Progression and retention via challenges, points, and loot crates\n- Referral-driven growth with on-chain earnings\n- Operational safety: pause, monitoring, incident response\n\n---\n\n## 2) Shipped Capabilities\n\n### Games (3 live)\n- **FlipYou** (spec 001) — 1v1, commit-reveal + SlotHashes fairness, custom wagers\n- **Pot Shot / Pot Shot** (spec 101) — Multiplayer weighted-entry pot shot, commit-reveal fairness\n- **Close Call** (spec 100) — Pari-mutuel BTC price prediction, Pyth oracle settlement, minute-boundary candle cache\n\n### On-Chain Programs\n- **Per-game programs**: FlipYou, Pot Shot, Close Call — each independently deployable\n- **Platform program**: PlatformConfig (fee BPS, treasury, pause state), admin-updatable via `update_platform_config`\n- **Shared Rust crate** (`solana/shared/`): Escrow helpers, lifecycle state machine, timeout logic, pause controls, commit-reveal verifier, fee calculation, constants\n- **Operational controls**: `set_paused` (per-game pause/unpause), `timeout_refund` (permissionless liveness guarantee), `force_close` (stuck round recovery)\n\n### Settlement & Workers\n- **PDA watcher**: WebSocket `onAccountChange` for instant join/settle detection\n- **Polling fallback**: 1s interval for resilience, ~3-5s total settlement latency\n- **Close Call clock**: Minute-boundary BTC price capture from Pyth Hermes, automatic round creation and settlement\n- **Retry worker**: Exponential backoff for failed settlement transactions\n- **Event worker**: Status transitions (scheduled -> active -> ended) on 10s poll; current implementation uses legacy Dogpile naming\n\n### Auth & Identity\n- **JWT auth** (spec 007) — Challenge-response via wallet signature, HS256 tokens\n- **Player profiles** (spec 008) — Auto-created on first auth, username with 30-day change cooldown\n- **Player stats**: Games played, total wagered, wins, win rate, win streaks (current + all-time), net PnL, per-game breakdown\n- **Public profiles**: Stats visible to other players (no wallet or transaction history exposed)\n- **Weekly leaderboard**: Volume-based ranking per game type with win rate and PnL\n\n### Fairness & Pricing\n- **Commit-reveal fairness** (spec 006): `SHA256(secret || entropy || PDA || algo_ver)`, public verification endpoints\n- **Wager value rate**: cached global conversion rate used for points USD conversion; current implementation reads SOL/USD from Pyth Hermes\n- **Fee structure**: 500 bps flat to single treasury, on-chain PlatformConfig canonical. CI guard: `scripts/check-fees.sh`\n\n### Reward & Retention\n- **Challenge engine** (spec 400) — Daily/weekly/onboarding challenges, template-based, adapter-driven\n- **Reward economy** (spec 401) — Generic points, multiplier, season, and event model; product labels stay display-only\n- **Points** — Season-scoped balance earned per $ wagered using cached global value rates and active multipliers\n- **Loot crates** — Random drops after settled games (points crates + SOL crates from reward pool)\n- **Reward pool** — Accounting-only ledger, configurable share of platform fees (default 20%)\n- **Events** — Scheduled modifier windows with boosted or overridden multipliers, admin-managed\n- **Completion bonus** — Meta-reward for completing all daily challenges (configurable)\n\n### Growth\n- **Referral system** (spec 300) — Unique codes/links, 1000 bps of fee as referral earnings, on-chain SOL claims, KOL rate overrides\n- **Onboarding chain** — 4-step guided first session (set nickname, play, win, try all game types)\n\n### Backend Infrastructure\n- **Async event queue** (spec 301) — Postgres-backed, `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`, handler registry, exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s), dead-letter after 3 attempts\n- **Event-driven pipeline** — `game.settled` → challenge progress + points + crate drops + pool funding; `profile.username_set` → onboarding challenge progress\n- **Admin API** — Campaign/challenge CRUD, reward config tuning, event scheduling, reward pool monitoring (X-Admin-Key auth)\n- **Rate limiting**: Per-wallet and global rate limits on game creation endpoints\n- **Health endpoint**: `GET /health` — DB connectivity, worker status, unsettled queue depth\n- **Transaction history**: Per-player ledger of on-chain deposits, payouts, refunds with game context\n\n### Cross-Repo Tooling\n- `scripts/verify` — Full lint + typecheck + test across all packages\n- `scripts/deploy-devnet.sh` — Build → deploy → IDL sync → config init → ID verification\n- `scripts/check-program-ids.sh` — Anchor.toml / declare_id! / IDL address consistency\n- `scripts/check-fees.sh` — Fee constant parity across Rust and TypeScript\n- `scripts/sync-idl` — Copy built IDLs from solana/target/ to backend anchor-client\n\n---\n\n## 3) Architecture Direction (Locked)\n\nDecisions are recorded in `docs/DECISIONS.md`. Key constraints:\n\n- **Chain**: Solana only. No multichain.\n- **Custody**: Non-custodial. All money movement on-chain.\n- **Programs**: Standard Anchor, per-game + shared crate. No BOLT ECS, no monolith program.\n- **Fairness**: Commit-reveal + SlotHashes (default). VRF optional for future games, not default infrastructure.\n- **Wallets**: Normal wallet-adapter flow. Privy/embedded wallets evaluated later.\n- **Frontend**: Separate project and team. Backend provides API contracts. See `docs/DECISIONS.md` (2026-04-02).\n- **Backend**: Hono API monolith with event-driven side-effects. Challenge engine extraction to separate service deferred (see `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`).\n\n---\n\n## 4) Trust Boundaries\n\n### On-Chain (source of truth)\n- All money movement (escrow, payout, refund, fee collection)\n- Round settlement outcomes\n- Payout eligibility and claim state\n- Platform config (fee rate, pause state)\n\n### Off-Chain (backend)\n- Secret generation and commitment\n- Settlement submission (permissionless on-chain, but backend holds the secret)\n- Player profiles, stats, transaction history\n- Challenge/reward evaluation and grant\n- Points and reward pool accounting\n- Referral tracking and claim processing\n\n### Rule\nIf it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n\n---\n\n## 5) Near-Term Direction\n\n### In progress\n- **Chat service** (spec 009) — Separate repo (`chat/`), global chat + event feed transport\n- **Events** — Scheduled, admin-managed. Infrastructure shipped under legacy Dogpile naming, needs generic reward-economy migration.\n\n### Next priorities\n- SOL crate payout production hardening (tech debt: review transfer handler before enabling)\n- Challenge pool rotation (M2: per-player daily draws from template pool)\n- Additional verification adapters (streak, volume, unique opponents)\n- KOL-triggered challenge campaigns\n- Quest completion leaderboard\n\n### Explicitly deferred\n- **Crash** (spec 002) — Deferred to Phase 2 (decision 2026-03-30). Real-time multiplier game needs different fairness model.\n- **Future game concepts** (specs 102-105) — Not ideated. Placeholders only.\n- **Custodial balance model** — Not planned.\n- **Multichain** — Not planned.\n- **Token utility / TGE mechanics** — Points are the pre-TGE signal. Token integration is post-launch.\n\n---\n\n## 6) Repo Ownership\n\n| Area | Repo | Ownership |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| On-chain programs | `solana/` submodule | This workspace |\n| Backend API + workers | `backend/` submodule | This workspace |\n| Chat service | `chat/` submodule | This workspace |\n| Telegram bot service | `telegram/` submodule | This workspace |\n| Docs, scripts, E2E | Root repo | This workspace |\n| Frontend | Separate repo | Separate team |\n| Waitlist | `waitlist/` | Separate repo (npm, DigitalOcean) |\n\n---\n\n## 7) Success Metrics\n\n- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n- Game round completion rate\n- Challenge completion rate and reward ROI (SOL spent per $ additional wager volume)\n- Referral conversion rate\n- Points/crate engagement (% of active players interacting with challenge UI)\n- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n\n---\n\n## 8) Spec Index\n\n### Shipped (Done)\n| Spec | Name | Notes |\n|------|------|-------|\n| 001 | FlipYou | Shipped, hybrid fairness |\n| 006 | Fairness Backend | Shipped |\n| 007 | JWT Session Auth | Shipped |\n| 008 | User Profile | Shipped (redesigned 2026-03-12) |\n| 100 | Close Call | Shipped, Pyth oracle |\n| 101 | Pot Shot | Shipped |\n| 200 | Visual Regression | Shipped (frontend deferred) |\n| 203 | E2E Integration | Active |\n| 300 | Referral System | Shipped |\n| 301 | Async Event Queue | Shipped |\n| 400 | Challenge Engine | Shipped M1 |\n\n### Active\n| Spec | Name | Notes |\n|------|------|-------|\n| 004 | Shared Infrastructure | Living doc, on-chain lifecycle patterns |\n| 009 | Chat | In progress, separate service |\n| 302 | Telegram Bot | Draft, stateless v1 bot + Telegram share flow |\n| 999 | Enhancements | Rolling backlog |\n\n### Deferred\n| Spec | Name | Notes |\n|------|------|-------|\n| 002 | Crash | Phase 2 (decision 2026-03-30) |\n| 102-105 | Future games | Not ideated, placeholders |\n\n### Out of Scope (frontend)\n| Spec | Name | Notes |\n|------|------|-------|\n| 204 | Multi-Page Flows | Frontend team |\n| 205 | Real Wallet | Frontend team |\n\n### Archived / Superseded\n| Spec | Name | Notes |\n|------|------|-------|\n| 003 | Platform Core | Superseded by DESIGN_REFERENCE.md |\n| 005 | Hybrid Fairness | Superseded by DECISIONS.md (2026-03-11) + spec 006 |\n| 201 | Unit Tests | Covered by FOUNDATIONS.md testing methodology |\n| 202 | Component Tests | Covered by FOUNDATIONS.md testing methodology |\n","numLines":206,"startLine":1,"totalLines":206}}}
